node.text:
It was an absolute honor joining @barramexico for their speaker series and having our CEO & Co-founder @berthagonzalezn host a “Women in the Industry” roundtable. Thank you @insiteevents, @yanaesque , and the two founders of Barra Mexico, @aracarvallo, and @_paulagarciam for sharing your inspirational story and words.
---
Fue un honor haber acompañado a @barramexico en su seminarios, donde nuestra Cofundadora y CEO berthagonzalezn participó en un roundtable acerca de las “Mujeres en la Industria”. Gracias a Sandra Vázquez, Yana Volfson, y las cofundadoras de Barra México, Ara Carvallo y Paula García, por compartir su historia y experiencia en la industria con nosotros. Conoce más sobre las historias de estas increíbles mujeres en nuestro IGTV.

#CasaDragones #SanMigueldeAllende #Tequila #BarraMexico2021

#Regram

Master mixologist @joseluisleon who joins us from Casa Dragones breaks down everything you need to know about tequila. He prepares 3 cocktails for National Tequila Day on Saturday, July 24th. Get orders in now at CasaDragones.com 🍸🍸🍹🍹
Cocktails José is making: Margarita Al Pastor; Watermelon Cooler; Yellow Summer Spritz
💃🏻💃🏻
At @mobysny with special guests owner @lincolnpilcher , @erikahalweil and @dylanbleue 💙💙
Recipes:
MARGARITA AL PASTOR
Combine Tequila Casa Dragones, Cointreau, fresh-squeezed lime juice, and taco mix, and ice in cocktail shaker. Rim your Old Fashioned glass with coriander salt. Shake + strain mixture over a 2-inch cube, and garnish with pineapple.
🍍
*For the taco mix: in a blender put pineapple juice, fresh coriander, basil and mint, a touch of green chili spicy + agave syrup to taste.
🌶
1.75 oz Tequila Casa Dragones Blanco
0.50 oz Cointreau
1 oz Fresh Squeezed Lime Juice
1.5 oz Pineapple Juice
🍍
1 Old Fashioned Glass
2-inch Ice Cube
1 Pineapple Triangle
0.20 oz Coriander Salt

WATERMELON COOLER
Combine Tequila Casa Dragones, Fino sherry, fresh-squeezed lemon juice, watermelon juice, and agave syrup, add ice in a cocktail shaker. Shake + strain mixture over a highball, garnish with watermelon.
🍉🍉
1 oz Tequila Casa Dragones Blanco
1 oz Fino Sherry
0.75 oz Lemon Juice
2.5 oz Watermelon Juice
0.5 oz Agave Syrup
1 Highball Glass

YELLOW SUMMER SPRITZ
Combine Casa Dragones Blanco, Chenin blanc white wine, pineapple juice and chamomile syrup in a cocktail shaker and dry shake. Add cocktail ice, shake. Pour ingredients into wine glass, top-off with sparking water, add pineapple wedge.

1 oz Tequila Casa Dragones Blanco
1 oz Chenin blanc white wine
1.5 oz pineapple juice
0.50 oz chamomile syrup
1 oz sparkling water
1 pineapple wedge
Cubed ice in white wine glass🌵🌵🌵

Executive @cheftravisstrickland of Los Angeles's contemporary restaurant @baltaire pairs Tequila Casa Dragones Joven with a charred bluefin tuna tostada.

Sourcing local ingredients such as Cara Cara oranges to create a citrus ponzu and a freshly-harvested avocado from Ojai, Chef Strickland approaches his pairing using only fresh ingredients that deliver the utmost quality. He drew inspiration from the smokiness of the charred tuna as he enjoys the way it marries to the complex, smooth, agave-forward profile of Casa Dragones Joven.

node.text:
Chef Matt Conroy and  Isabel Coss pair Casa Dragones Joven with two of their favorite cuisines from Washington DC's Partisan-inspired restaurant, Lutèce's. 

Chef @Conroy_Matt finds that the silky body and subtle vanilla notes of Casa Dragones Joven, when enjoyed with the buttery texture and brininess of his pan-seared Maine sea scallops, introduce a heavenly marriage. @ChabelaCoss draws inspiration from the delicate floral aromas and complex profile of Casa Dragones Joven. She finds that this expression compliments and does not overpower the velvety texture of her elegant Fraises et Creme tart. Together this culinary experience is one you will remember for time to come. 

If you find yourself taking in the beauty of old Georgetown, be sure to stop in, say hello, and try these beautiful pairings @Lutecedc.

We’re thrilled to join our friends at @hotelmatilda as they officially present the newest addition to their family, Mui Ramen Bar. @monkeymixology had the opportunity to talk to their amazing bartender @yljonvaz as he crafts the 50 Dragons of Grey cocktail with Casa Dragones Blanco, and the Aldama 53 with Casa Dragones Añejo Barrel Blend, and of course try their amazing Shoyu signature Ramen, with belly chashu. If you find yourself in San Miguel de Allende, make sure to add this new spot to your itinerary.

Cocktail recipes:

Aldama 53
20 ml Casa Dragones Añejo
30 ml Porto Wine
30 ml Dry Vermouth
10 ml Lime Cordial

Add ingredients to a large mixing glass with ice and stir. Serve on an old fashioned glass with a large ice cube, and add lemon twist.

50 Dragons of Grey
30 ml Casa Dragones Blanco
100 ml Milk Punch

To make the milk punch, add raspberries, lime, maracuya, black tea, and passionfruit and milk. Slow-strain with a coffee filter.

Add ingredients to a mixing glass with ice and stir. Serve on a spotty old fashioned glass, with a large ice cube, and add a lemon twist.

TANE x Casa Dragones se complacen en presentar “The San Miguel de Allende Edition”.
 
@tane.mx y Tequila Casa Dragones, se unen por cuarta ocasión para crear La Edición San Miguel de Allende, un nuevo set de edición limitada y numerada a 16 unidades, elaborado con atención al detalle y una calidad excepcional que caracteriza a ambas casas. Este nuevo set rinde tributo a La Casa Dragones en San Miguel de Allende. Esta edición exclusiva es un ejemplo de la excelencia de la artesanía mexicana y presenta una historia que honra la tradición y el lujo mexicano contemporáneo.
 
TANE fue fundada en 1942, durante casi 80 años ha creado de forma continua y consistente impresionantes piezas de joyería para mujeres y hombres, objetos contemporáneos de la más alta calidad, así como piezas de arte dignas de museo. La mano de obra de TANE es ampliamente considerada como insuperable, y cada pieza está hecha a mano por los talentosos artesanos de la compañía en sus propios talleres en México. 

Conoce más sobre este exclusivo set a través de nuestro Concierge@CasaDragones.com

#CasaDragones #SanMigueldeAllende #Tequila #EdicionLimitada

Our programming during @barramexico included competitions, parties, mixology pop-ups, and a wide variety of experiences with our three tequila styles around San Miguel de Allende, co-hosted by some of our most important local partners. Guests were able to enjoy mixology classes led by Fabiola Padilla and Adrian Evans at @bekeb_sma and @monkeybar.sma, culinary experiences including our Flight Program with small bites and special pairing dinners with @aperimx and @moxirestaurant restaurants, as well as private intimate Mixology Residencies and profesional tastings at our Casa Dragones Tasting Room. Additionally we were able to offer for the very first time Cigar Pairings at the Casa Dragones Cigar Bar in @liveaquasanmiguel, where guests could enjoy a selection of cigars to pair with Casa Dragones Añejo Barrel Blend. You can book any of our available experiences for your next visit to San Miguel de Allende in our website’s Booking System.

Nuestra programación durante Barra México incluyó competencias de mixología, fiestas, pop-ups con bartenders y un rango de experiencias con nuestros tres estilos de tequila en algunos de los lugares más importantes de San Miguel de Allende. Los invitados disfrutaron de clases de mixología con Fabiola Padilla en @bekeb_sma y Adrian Evans en @monkeybar.sma, experiencias culinarias con aperitivos y cenas maridaje en @aperimx y @moxirestaurant, así como también catas de tequila y cócteles en nuestro Tasting Room. Además, presentamos por primera vez nuestra experiencia de puros y Casa Dragones Añejo en @liveaquasanmiguel. Si quieres hacer una reserva para cualquiera de nuestras experiencias, visita nuestro sistema de reservas en el sitio web.

When we started the process of producing our añejo tequila, Casa Dragones Barrel Blend, we went on a journey of taste to find the perfect blend of wood to complement—not overpower—our signature taste. We collaborated with one of France’s most respected cooperages and dedicated two years to work closely together to craft our custom-made wood barrels.
—-
Cuando empezamos con la producción de nuestro tequila añejo, Casa Dragones Añejo, emprendimos un recorrido de sabor para encontrar la mezcla perfecta de madera para complementar el sabor característico de nuestro tequila. Colaboramos con una de las tonelerías más respetadas de Francia, dedicando dos años de trabajo para explorar el maridaje perfecto de la madera para nuestras barricas.

node.text:
Experience the nuances of Casa Dragones Añejo Barrel Blend. The new French Oak barrel provides roundness, respecting the minerality of our soil and imparting light spicy notes such as licorice, clover, and light vanilla notes. The new American Oak barrel provides depth and aromatic intensity. Together, they create infinite richness and an agave-forward taste profile that is both elegant and smooth.
---
Descubre los matices de Casa Dragones Añejo Barrel Blend. La madera francesa imparte redondez y un sabor ligeramente especiado, respetando las propiedades minerales de nuestra tierra. Las barricas de roble americano muestran la complejidad del agave y brindando una hermosa intensidad aromática. El maridaje artesanal de ambas barricas celebra las notas predominantes de agave, elegantes y suaves, que revelan un perfil infinitamente rico y matizado.
